### ============================================
### SAP SuccessFactors RBP Audit Tool - Complete Test Suite
### ============================================
### Base URL: http://localhost:4004
### ============================================

### ============================================
### 1. SERVICE DISCOVERY
### ============================================

### 1.1 Get Service Document
GET http://localhost:4004/

### 1.2 Get AuditExecutionService Metadata
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/$metadata

### 1.3 Get AuditReportingService Metadata
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/$metadata

### ============================================
### 2. USER MANAGEMENT
### ============================================

### 2.1 Sync Users from SuccessFactors
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/syncUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 2.2 Get Users (with pagination)
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/getUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0,
    "status": "active"
}

### 2.3 Search Users by Name
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/getUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "search": "admin",
    "top": 10,
    "skip": 0
}

### 2.4 Search Users by Partial Name
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/getUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "search": "singh",
    "top": 10,
    "skip": 0
}

### 2.4 Get Users from Reporting Service (this is an entity, so GET works)
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Users?$top=10


### ============================================
### 3. AUDIT RUNS - CREATE & LIST
### ============================================

### 3.1 Create Full Audit Run(date error)
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Weekly Full Audit",
    "description": "Full audit of all permission groups and roles",
    "mode": "FULL",
    "extractGroups": true,
    "extractRoles": true,
    "sampleGroupSize": 0,
    "sampleMemberSize": 0,
    "sampleRoleSize": 0
}

### 3.2 Create Sample Audit Run (for testing) (date error)
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test Sample Audit",
    "description": "Sample audit for testing",
    "mode": "SAMPLE",
    "extractGroups": true,
    "extractRoles": true,
    "sampleGroupSize": 5,
    "sampleMemberSize": 10,
    "sampleRoleSize": 3
}

### 3.3 Get All Audit Runs
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns

### 3.4 List Audit Runs (with filters)
# @prompt status (optional: CREATED, RUNNING, COMPLETED, FAILED)
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/listAuditRuns?status=COMPLETED&top=10&skip=0

### 3.5 Get Specific Audit Run by ID
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns({{auditRunID}})

### ============================================
### 4. AUDIT STATUS & MONITORING
### ============================================

### 4.1 Get Audit Status(not working)
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/getAuditStatus
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}


### 4.2 Wait for audit to complete (check every 5 seconds)
# Use the status from above to check progress

### ============================================
### 5. GROUP ANALYSIS
### ============================================

### 5.1 Get All Groups
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}&$top=20

### 5.2 Get Static Groups
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$filter=groupType eq 'STATIC'&$top=20

### 5.3 Get Dynamic Groups
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$filter=groupType eq 'DYNAMIC'&$top=20

### 5.4 Get Group Details (with metrics)
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getGroupDetails
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "groupType": null,
    "minMembers": 0,
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0
}

### 5.5 Get Group Size Analysis
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getGroupSizeAnalysis
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### ============================================
### 6. USER ACCESS ANALYSIS
### ============================================

### 6.1 Get User Details (with group counts)
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getUserDetails
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "status": "active",
    "minGroupCount": 0,
    "department": null,
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0
}

### 6.2 Get User Access Analysis
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getUserAccessAnalysis
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "top": 20
}

### 6.3 Get High Risk Users
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getHighRiskUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "minRiskScore": 5,
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0
}

### 6.4 Get Inactive Users with Access
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getInactiveUsersWithAccess
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "riskCategory": null,
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0
}

### ============================================
### 7. ROLE ANALYSIS
### ============================================

### 7.1 Get All Roles
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Roles?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}&$top=20

### 7.2 Get Role Details
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRoleDetails
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "usageStatus": null,
    "top": 20,
    "skip": 0
}

### 7.3 Get Role Coverage Analysis
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRoleCoverageAnalysis
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### 7.4 Get Unused Roles
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/UnusedRoles?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}

### ============================================
### 8. GROUP-ROLE MATRIX
### ============================================

### 8.1 Get Group-Role Matrix
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getGroupRoleMatrix
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "top": 50,
    "skip": 0
}

### ============================================
### 9. USER-ROLE MAPPINGS
### ============================================

### 9.1 Get All User-Role Mappings
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/UserRoleMappings?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}&$top=20

### 9.2 Get User-Role Matrix
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getUserRoleMatrix
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "userName": null,
    "roleName": null,
    "department": null,
    "top": 50,
    "skip": 0
}

### 9.3 Get Users by Role
# @prompt auditRunID
# @prompt roleId
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getUsersByRole
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "roleId": "{{roleId}}",
    "top": 50,
    "skip": 0
}

### 9.4 Get Roles by User
# @prompt auditRunID
# @prompt userName
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRolesByUser
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "userName": "{{userName}}",
    "top": 50,
    "skip": 0
}

### ============================================
### 10. RISK DASHBOARD & EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
### ============================================

### 10.1 Get Risk Dashboard
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRiskDashboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### 10.2 Get Executive Summary
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getExecutiveSummary
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### ============================================
### 11. MULTI-GROUP USERS (Risk Analysis)
### ============================================

### 11.1 Get All Multi-Group Users
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/MultiGroupUsers?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}&$top=20

### 11.2 Get High Risk Multi-Group Users
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/MultiGroupUsers?$filter=riskLevel eq 'High'&$top=20

### ============================================
### 12. GROUP MEMBERSHIPS
### ============================================

### 12.1 Get All Group Members
# @prompt auditRunID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/GroupMembers?$filter=auditRunID_ID eq {{auditRunID}}&$top=50

### 12.2 Get Members of Specific Group
# @prompt groupID
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/GroupMembers?$filter=groupID eq '{{groupID}}'&$top=50

### ============================================
### 13. DELETE & CLEANUP
### ============================================

### 13.1 Delete Audit Run
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/deleteAuditRun
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### ============================================
### 14. EXPORT FUNCTIONS
### ============================================

### 14.1 Export Full Audit Data
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/exportAuditData
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "format": "JSON"
}

### 14.2 Export Specific Report
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/exportReport
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "reportType": "groups",
    "format": "CSV"
}

### ============================================
### 15. BATCH REQUEST - Multiple Queries
### ============================================

POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/$batch
Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary=batch_123

--batch_123
Content-Type: application/http
Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary

GET Groups?$top=5 HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:4004


--batch_123
Content-Type: application/http
Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary

GET Users?$top=5 HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:4004


--batch_123
Content-Type: application/http
Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary

GET Roles?$top=5 HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:4004


--batch_123--

### ============================================
### 16. QUICK TEST SEQUENCE
### ============================================

### Step 1: Sync Users (first run)
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/syncUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Step 2: Create Sample Audit Run
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Quick Test Audit",
    "description": "Quick test run",
    "mode": "SAMPLE",
    "extractGroups": true,
    "extractRoles": true,
    "sampleGroupSize": 3,
    "sampleMemberSize": 5,
    "sampleRoleSize": 2
}

### Step 3: Get Audit Status (use the ID from Step 2)
# @prompt auditRunID
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/getAuditStatus
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### Step 4: Wait for COMPLETED status (check every 5 seconds)

### Step 5: View Groups
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$top=10

### Step 6: View Users
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Users?$top=10

### Step 7: Get Risk Dashboard
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRiskDashboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### Step 8: Get Executive Summary
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getExecutiveSummary
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### Step 9: Get High Risk Users
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getHighRiskUsers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}",
    "minRiskScore": 5,
    "top": 10,
    "skip": 0
}

### Step 10: Get Group Size Analysis
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getGroupSizeAnalysis
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### Step 11: Get Role Coverage Analysis
POST http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/getRoleCoverageAnalysis
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "auditRunID": "{{auditRunID}}"
}

### ============================================
### 17. ADVANCED QUERIES
### ============================================

### 17.1 Get Groups with Member Count > 50
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$filter=totalMemberCount gt 50&$top=20

### 17.2 Get Users with Risk Level High
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/MultiGroupUsers?$filter=riskLevel eq 'High'&$expand=User

### 17.3 Get Roles with No Target Population
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Roles?$expand=RoleTargetPopulations&$filter=RoleTargetPopulations/any(r: false)

### 17.4 Get Group Members with User Details
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/GroupMembers?$expand=User&$top=20

### 17.5 Count Total Groups
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups/$count

### 17.6 Count Total Users
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Users/$count

### 17.7 Count High Risk Users
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/MultiGroupUsers/$count?$filter=riskLevel eq 'High'

### ============================================
### 18. DEBUGGING ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 18.1 Check if Groups are loaded
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Groups?$top=5

### 18.2 Check if Users are loaded
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Users?$top=5

### 18.3 Check if Roles are loaded
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/Roles?$top=5

### 18.4 Check if MultiGroupUsers are loaded
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/MultiGroupUsers?$top=5

### 18.5 Check if UnusedRoles are loaded
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPReport/UnusedRoles?$top=5

### 18.6 Check Audit Execution Service
GET http://localhost:4004/SuccessFactorRBPAudit/AuditRuns?$top=5